<div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 mt-16">
  <DisplayTitle level={1}>V. Integration Principles</DisplayTitle>
  
  <div class="relative mb-16">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-900 to-indigo-900 opacity-10 blur-xl"></div>
    <div class="relative">
      <CardGrid columns={2} gap="2rem">
        <Card title="Seeking Mutual Benefit" color="purple" icon="🤝">
          Focusing on reforms and initiatives that provide clear advantages to all member states, fostering a spirit of collective progress.
        </Card>

        <Card title="Leveraging Economies of Scale" color="indigo" icon="📈">
          Prioritizing European-wide digital solutions that are more cost-effective when developed collectively, nurturing a new generation of technocrats coding for the EU.
        </Card>

        <Card title="Building a Common Culture" color="purple" icon="🌍">
          Using a shared language and media landscape to foster a truly European identity alongside national cultures.
        </Card>

        <Card title="Quality of Life Through Reform" color="indigo" icon="✨">
          Pursuing radical reforms and shifting competencies to the EU level to address challenges too big for individual nations, focusing on improving life for all Europeans rather than austerity.
        </Card>
      </CardGrid>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 mt-16 mb-12">
  <DisplayTitle level={1}>VI. Benefits</DisplayTitle>
  
  <div class="relative mb-16">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900 to-indigo-900 opacity-10 blur-xl"></div>
    <div class="relative">
      <CardGrid columns={3} gap="1.5rem">
        <Card title="Benefits for European Integration" color="blue" icon="🇪🇺">
          Highlighting the advantages of a more unified Europe, fostering collaboration and shared growth across all member states.
        </Card>

        <Card title="Benefits for Germany" color="indigo" icon="🇩🇪">
          Exploring how Germany can leverage its industrial strength to lead in robotics and digital transformation, enhancing its economic position.
        </Card>

        <Card title="Benefits for France" color="blue" icon="🇫🇷">
          Discussing France's role in cultural integration and leadership in digital governance, strengthening its influence in the EU.
        </Card>

        <Card title="Benefits for Southern Europe" color="indigo" icon="🏛️">
          Addressing economic disparities and promoting sustainable development through enhanced logistics and digital services.
        </Card>

        <Card title="Benefits for Scandinavia" color="blue" icon="❄️">
          Leveraging technological advancements and environmental initiatives to drive innovation and sustainability.
        </Card>

        <Card title="Benefits for Central Europe" color="indigo" icon="🏭">
          Utilizing the region's skilled workforce to spearhead robotics and software development, boosting economic growth.
        </Card>

        <Card title="Benefits for Businesses" color="blue" icon="💼">
          Facilitating seamless operations across borders, reducing costs, and opening new markets for European enterprises.
        </Card>

        <Card title="Benefits for Citizens" color="indigo" icon="👨‍👩‍👧‍👦">
          Improving quality of life through streamlined services, enhanced mobility, and increased opportunities for personal growth.
        </Card>

        <Card title="Benefits for eCommerce" color="blue" icon="🛒">
          Enabling faster, more reliable logistics and payment systems, fostering a thriving online marketplace.
        </Card>

        <Card title="Benefits for IT Startups" color="indigo" icon="💻">
          Providing a supportive ecosystem for innovation, with access to a unified market and collaborative development opportunities.
        </Card>

        <Card title="Benefits for European Security" color="blue" icon="🛡️">
          Strengthening collective defense and cybersecurity measures, ensuring a safer environment for all Europeans.
        </Card>

        <Card title="Benefits for the Information Economy" color="indigo" icon="📊">
          Positioning Europe as a leader in data-driven industries, harnessing the power of big data and AI for economic growth.
        </Card>
      </CardGrid>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 my-16">
  <DisplayTitle level={1}>Why Digital Reform Is Necessary</DisplayTitle>
  
  <div class="relative">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-r from-teal-900 to-blue-900 opacity-10 blur-xl"></div>
    <div class="relative">
      <WhyDigitalReform color="teal" />
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 my-16">
  <DisplayTitle level={1}>Common Questions</DisplayTitle>
  
  <div class="relative">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-900 to-indigo-900 opacity-10 blur-xl"></div>
    <div class="relative">
      <FAQ 
        color="indigo"
        items={[
          {
            question: "Why do we need yet another European integration project?",
            answer: "Unlike previous integration efforts, this vision focuses on practical, tangible benefits for all Europeans rather than abstract political concepts. By focusing on language, digital infrastructure, and robotic reindustrialization, we address the actual challenges facing Europe in an era of global competition and technological change."
          },
          {
            question: "Isn't English as a second language unfair to non-English speaking countries?",
            answer: "This proposal recognizes that English is already the de facto international language of business, science, and technology. Rather than starting from zero with a new language, we're acknowledging reality and formalizing it to reduce barriers. National languages remain primary, with English as a practical addition that enables greater European-wide communication and opportunity."
          },
          {
            question: "How will these changes benefit ordinary citizens?",
            answer: "Citizens will gain access to streamlined public services in multiple languages, enjoy faster cross-border shipping, benefit from enhanced AI-powered healthcare, access lifetime educational opportunities, and experience greater job mobility throughout Europe. The vision aims to create a Europe where everyday life becomes simpler, more efficient, and more prosperous for all."
          },
          {
            question: "What if Germany or other powerful countries don't agree?",
            answer: "If certain countries choose not to participate initially, this vision could begin as an Intermarium 2.0 project with countries like Poland, Ukraine, Romania, and Scandinavian nations. The benefits of integration would likely become apparent quickly, encouraging others to join. The proposal creates such clear mutual advantages that even skeptical countries would have strong incentives to participate."
          },
          {
            question: "How would this be funded?",
            answer: "This vision fundamentally changes how we think about funding. Rather than focusing on redistribution, it leverages economies of scale and efficiency gains. By building common digital systems once (instead of 27 times), sharing development costs, and optimizing processes, we create value that pays for itself through increased productivity, reduced waste, and economic growth."
          },
          {
            question: "How long would implementation take?",
            answer: "This is a long-term vision with a 15-20 year implementation timeline, with different components being rolled out in stages. Some elements, like digital payment systems or unified logistics standards, could be implemented relatively quickly (3-5 years), while others like full language integration would follow a longer timeline with gradual milestones."
          }
        ]}
      />
    </div>
  </div>
</div>


<div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 my-16">
  <DisplayTitle level={1}>About the Author</DisplayTitle>
  
  <div class="relative">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900 to-purple-900 opacity-10 blur-xl"></div>
    <div class="relative">
      <Author color="purple" />
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 my-16 mb-24">
  <DisplayTitle level={1}>Stay Updated</DisplayTitle>
  
  <div class="relative">
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900 to-indigo-900 opacity-10 blur-xl"></div>
    <div class="relative bg-blue-900/30 border border-blue-700/50 rounded-xl p-8 shadow-lg">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Subscribe to Our Newsletter</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-300 mb-6">Join our community of forward-thinking Europeans. Get updates on the latest developments and be part of shaping Europe's digital future.</p>
        
        <form class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center mb-4">
          <input 
            type="email" 
            placeholder="Your email address" 
            class="px-4 py-3 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-white focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500 focus:border-transparent w-full sm:w-auto sm:flex-1 max-w-md"
          />
          <button 
            type="submit" 
            class="px-6 py-3 bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-500 text-white font-medium rounded-lg transition-colors duration-300"
          >
            Subscribe
          </button>
        </form>
        <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">We respect your privacy. Unsubscribe at any time.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

</Layout>